fields.engineering_tactics:
(1) AUTHOR THE PLAN BEFORE WRITING ANALYTICS CODE. Spreadsheet (rows = events, columns = name, properties, types, when_emitted, owner, version) OR Avo / Iteratively / Segment Protocols / hand-rolled TypeScript file. (2) NAMING CONVENTION: snake_case verb-object pattern, e.g., `onboarding_step_viewed`, `onboarding_step_completed`, `onboarding_step_abandoned`. Reserve `_completed` for explicit user action; `_viewed` for screen render; `_abandoned` for back-nav or app-kill mid-step. (3) CANONICAL ONBOARDING EVENTS (minimum coverage):
- `onboarding_started` { ad_variant, locale, archetype, anonymous_id }
- `onboarding_step_viewed` { step_id, step_index, total_steps, step_kind, ad_variant, locale, time_on_step_ms }
- `onboarding_step_completed` { step_id, step_index, step_kind, answer_value_hash, time_on_step_ms }
- `onboarding_step_abandoned` { step_id, step_index, time_on_step_ms, abandon_type: 'back' | 'app_kill' | 'inactivity' }
- `onboarding_step_back_navigated` { from_step_id, to_step_id }
- `onboarding_progress_visible` { current_step, total_steps, percent_complete }
- `personalization_token_set` { token_name, source_step_id }
- `personalization_token_stitched` { token_name, target_step_id }
- `ai_plan_reveal_started` { plan_request_id, context_size_bytes }
- `ai_plan_reveal_completed` { plan_id, latency_ms, model_used }
- `ai_plan_reveal_failed` { reason, retry_count }
- `mid_onboarding_review_prompted` { step_id }
- `mid_onboarding_review_action` { action: 'rate' | 'dismiss' | 'maybe_later' }
- `paywall_shown` { paywall_id, plans_displayed, ad_variant, source: 'onboarding' }
- `paywall_purchased` { sku, price_locale, price_amount, currency }
- `paywall_dismissed_with_winback_shown` { winback_offer_id }
- `winback_purchased` { sku, original_paywall_id }
- `push_primer_shown` { source_step_id }
- `push_native_dialog_shown`, `push_opted_in`, `push_opted_out`
- `att_dialog_shown`, `att_authorized`, `att_denied`
- `onboarding_completed` { total_time_ms, total_steps_completed, final_step_id }
- `onboarding_resumed_from_server` { last_step_id, days_since_abandonment }
(4) PROPERTIES: include consistent superproperties on every event — { app_version, os, os_version, device_model, locale, anonymous_id, user_id (when known), session_id, experiment_variants, feature_flags }. (5) PII / privacy: never include free-text user input as event property; use hashes (SHA-256 of value, last 8 chars) for answer values where you need uniqueness without content. (6) SCHEMA-AS-CODE: define events as TypeScript discriminated union; analytics SDK enforces schema at compile time. EXAMPLE:
```typescript
export type AnalyticsEvent =
  | { name: 'onboarding_step_viewed'; props: StepViewedProps }
  | { name: 'onboarding_step_completed'; props: StepCompletedProps }
  | { name: 'paywall_shown'; props: PaywallShownProps };
export function track<E extends AnalyticsEvent>(event: E): void { ... }
```
(7) AUTO-CAPTURE COMPLEMENT: integrate UXCam OR Heap for full session replay + auto-captured screen events; treat as exploratory layer, not source-of-truth. Explicit events drive funnels and KPIs. (8) VALIDATION: integrate Avo / Segment Protocols on CI to fail builds where event names / properties don't match plan. (9) EVOLUTION: bump event version on schema change; deprecate old events with sunset date; never silently change event semantics. (10) DASHBOARD CONVENTION: every event has a 'home dashboard' linked from the plan doc. (11) OWNERSHIP: each event has a named owner (PM or eng lead) responsible for keeping its semantics stable. (12) DEBOUNCE / RATE-LIMITING: high-frequency events (scroll, hover) sampled or batched. Onboarding events are inherently low-frequency — emit fully.
